erleden","0890–Female":"0890–Overleden","0985":"0985","0930":"0930","985 (?)":"0985","0970":"0970","930":"0930","1024":"1024","0890":"0890","Abt 930":"circa 0930","0967":"0967","0900":"0900","Wales":"Wales, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Merionethshire, Wales":"Merionethshire, Wales"},"en":{"930–985 (?)":"0930–0985","0930–0985":"0930–0985","0967–Male":"0967–Deceased","0970–1024":"0970–1024","–Male":"Deceased","0900–Male":"0900–Deceased","0890–Female":"0890–Deceased","0985":"0985","0930":"0930","985 (?)":"0985","0970":"0970","930":"0930","1024":"1024","0890":"0890","Abt 930":"about 0930","0967":"0967","0900":"0900","Wales":"Wales, United Kingdom","Merionethshire, Wales":"Merionethshire, Wales","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Ap","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["German: variant of   Abt  .","Jewish (eastern Ashkenazic): habitational name from Apt, the Yiddish name of Opatów in Świętokrzyskie Voivodeship, Poland. The placename (in German, Yiddish, and Polish) is from a root meaning ‘abbot’, the place having been named for the local abbey. Compare   Abt  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Abt","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Helmut, Horst, Johann, Kurt.","German and Dutch: from Middle Low German or Middle Dutch <i>abt</i> ‘abbot’, hence a metonymic occupational name for a servant of an abbot or a nickname for someone thought to resemble an abbot in some way. In some instances it may have been a topographic or habitational name referring to a house named with this word.","Jewish (eastern Ashkenazic): variant of   Abt  , a habitational name from Opatów in Poland."]},{"name":"Apter","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Jewish Avrohom, Bronya, Eliezer, Naftali.","Jewish (Ashkenazic): habitational name for someone from Apt (see   Apt  ).","English: habitational name from Aptor in Marldon, Devon, composed of Old English <i>uppe</i> ‘up, above’ + <i>torr</i> ‘rocky outcrop’."]}]},{"name":"Llew","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["German: perhaps a variant of <b>Plewe</b>, a habitational name from a place so named in Brandenburg.","English: variant of <b>Plaw</b>, a topographic name for someone who lived by a place where sports and games were played, from Middle English <i>plaghe</i>, <i>plawe</i>, <i>pleie</i>, <i>ploghe</i>, <i>plowe</i> (Old English <i>plega</i>, <i>plæga</i>, <i>plaga</i>) ‘play, sport, game, merriment’ and by transference ‘play-place’.","English: northern variant of <b>Plow</b>, itself a variant of   Plough   ‘plow’."],"variants":[{"name":"Plough","meanings":["English: from Middle English <i>plo(u)gh</i>, <i>plou(w)</i> ‘plow’, presumably used as a metonymic occupational name for a plowman."]}]},{"name":"Llud","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English:","nickname for a noisy person, from Middle English<i>lude</i> ‘loud’ (Old English <i>hlūd</i>), perhaps in partpreserving the Old English byname <i>Hlūda</i> that Ekwallpostulates to explain the placenames Loudham (Suffolk) and Lowdham(Nottinghamshire).","topographic name for someone who lived by a roaring stream, Old English <i>hlūde</i> or <i>hl̄de</i> literally ‘the loud one’, or a habitational name from any of the places called from <i>hl̄de</i>, for example Lyde in Herefordshire and Somerset."],"variants":[{"name":"Louth","meanings":["English: habitational name from Louth in Lincolnshire, socalled from its position on the river Lud (Old English<i>Hlūde</i>, meaning ‘the loud one’).","Irish: when not of English origin (see 1 above), probably a shortened and altered form of   McLeod  . Compare   McLouth  ."]},{"name":"Lyde","meanings":["Transferred use of the mainly Scottish surname, in origin a local name for someone who came ‘from the island’ (Anglo-Norman <i>de l'isle</i>). (The island in question would in many cases have been an area of higher, dry ground in a marsh or fen, rather than in a sea or river.) There may have been some confusion with   Lyall ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Llud Ap Llew was born in 0930, in Merionethshire, Wales, his father, Llew ap Llyminod, was 31 and his mother, llyminiod Angel Llewelyn, was 40. He had at least 3 sons. He died in 0985, in Wales, United Kingdom, at the age of 55."},"et":{"930–985 (?)":"0930–0985","0930–0985":"0930–0985","0967–Male":"0967–Surnud","0970–1024":"0970–1024","–Male":"Surnud","0900–Male":"0900–Surnud","0890–Female":"0890–Surnud","0985":"0985","0930":"0930","985 (?)":"0985","0970":"0970","930":"0930","1024":"1024","0890":"0890","Abt 930":"umbes 0930","0967":"0967","0900":"0900","Wales":"Wales, United Kingdom","Merionethshire, Wales":"Merionethshire, Wales"},"fi":{"930–985 (?)":"0930–0985","0930–0985":"0930–0985","0967–Male":"0967–Kuollut","0970–1024":"0970–1024","–Male":"Kuollut","0900–Male":"0900–Kuollut","0890–Female":"0890–Kuollut","0985":"0985","0930":"0930","985 (?)":"0985","0970":"0970","930":"0930","1024":"1024","0890":"0890","Abt 930":"noin 0930","0967":"0967","0900":"0900","Wales":"Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Merionethshire, Wales":"Merionethshire, Wales"},"fr":{"930–985 (?)":"0930–0985","0930–0985":"0930–0985","0967–Male":"0967–Décédé","0970–1024":"0970–1024","–Male":"Décédé","0900–Male":"0900–Décédé","0890–Female":"0890–Décédée","0985":"0985","0930":"0930","985 (?)":"0985","0970":"0970","930":"0930","1024":"1024","0890":"0890","Abt 930":"environ 0930","0967":"0967","0900":"0900","Wales":"Pays de Galles, Royaume-Uni","Merionethshire, Wales":"Merionethshire, Galles","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Llud Ap Llew est né en 0930, à Merionethshire, Galles, son père, Llew ap Llyminod, avait 31 ans et sa mère, llyminiod Angel Llewelyn, avait 40 ans. Il a eu au moins 3 fils. Il est décédé en 0985, à Pays de Galles, Royaume-Uni, à l’âge de 55 ans."},"de":{"930–985 (?)":"0930–0985","0930–0985":"0930–0985","0967–Male":"0967–Verstorben","0970–1024":"0970–1024","–